# Testing Patterns

## Setup

Jest with jsdom environment (set per-file via `/** @jest-environment jsdom */` directive). Three test suites: `dom`, `universal`, and `ssr`.

Import runtime directly from source:

```javascript
import * as r from "../../src/client";
import { createSignal } from "@solidjs/signals";
```

## Test Projects

- `test/dom/` — Client-side DOM tests (element rendering, events, styles, classes, SVG, spreads, conditionals)
- `test/universal/` — Universal renderer tests
- `test/ssr/` — Server-side rendering and hydration tests

Each project has its own Jest transform configuration (`test/transform-dom.js`, `test/transform-universal.js`, etc.) that configures the babel plugin for the appropriate output mode.

## Conventions

- Tests use JSX — transforms are applied via the test-specific babel configs
- Runtime functions are imported as `r` namespace: `r.render()`, `r.insert()`, `r.template()`, `r.delegateEvents()`
- Reactive primitives come from `@solidjs/signals` directly
- DOM assertions use `innerHTML`, `textContent`, `querySelector`
- Spy/mock tracking via `jest.fn()`

## Commands

- `pnpm test` (from package dir) — `jest --no-cache`
- `pnpm test:coverage` — `jest --coverage --no-cache`
- `pnpm test` (from root) — runs all package tests via Lerna
